node.text:
Last week I had the honour of talking to Dr Vandana Shiva, the world renowned author, activist, eco-feminist and physicist, for @MyEcoResolution. Over the hour I learnt about the destruction caused by corporate globalisation, industrial agriculture and their links with colonialism. Vandana explained that that small farms are the future and we must all participate in the movement towards agriculture, economies and ways of being that respect the ecosystems on which we all rely. 

To watch the full interview go to the link in @myecoresolution bio and subscribe to the YouTube channel!

EcoResolution is also launching a Global Network of ChangeMakers to support, enable and motivate those engaging in land-based work with a focus on restoring ecosystems, growing food and improving community wellbeing. If you would like to join go to @MyEcoResolution to register!

node.text: In our culture, we are told that if we’re beautiful, if we’re skinny, if we’re successful, famous, if we fit in, if everyone loves us, that we’ll be happy. But that’s not entirely true. The most important journey that I think all of us will go through is the journey to find ourselves and find our truth, to find who we are and what makes us happy.  @womensprideofficial
